page.title: 19It's a beautiful boy
page.content: He has finally arrived!Cornwalls first test tube baby,Samuel Joshua Strick bounced into the world at 2.15 on Saturday morning a beautiful healthy nine and a half pounder. And for parents,Terri and Jimmy the birth at Treliske Hospital Truro,ended nine long years of frustration and anxiety, but both agreed he was well worth the wait. Everything went well during the six hour labour and Sams progress was monitored every inch of the way.And for dad Jimmy the moment of his arrival was the culmination of all their hopes and dreams. Forgotten were all the problems they had already had.Both Terri and Jimmy were looking foreward to taking Sam back to their home in St.Levan as soon as possible.
